  "description": [
    "BROTHER SAFE INJURED GIRI ISJUPPY Rejoicing that her baby brother had escaped Injury in the auto mobile crash that seriously hurt her right eye Gwendolen Freese 7 today bravely faced a possible operation at Episcopal Eye Ear and Throat Hospital as doctors fought to save the sight of the member Gwendolyn was injured when the automobile of her father Russell Freese of the 3900 block New Hampshire Ave N W collided with another machine at Fourth and K Sts N W The girl was driven to Casualty Hospital by John A Oliver 28 of the first block Pershing Ave N E driver of the car that struck her fathers auto The girls father carried her inside the hospital Quickly leaving the hospital Freese says he saw Oliver starting away He gave chase he says catching him a short distance away and turned him over to Ninth pre cinct policemen who charged him with leaving after colliding The greatest concern of Gwen dolyn on reaching the operating table was whether her ninemonth old brother Russell Freese jr had been injured She was riding with him on the rear seat of the Freese car when the accident occurred I dont care about"
